<p>
Provisioning time for a blank VPS is usually less than <strong>one minute</strong>.
</p>

<div>
  <div class='form-section-header-prominent'>Server Size:</div>

  <% VirtualMachine.plans['vps'].sort_by { |k, v| v['mrc'] }.each do |k, plan| %>
    <input type='radio' id='plan_<%= k %>' name='plan' value='<%= k %>' <%= k == 'small' ? 'checked' : '' %>>
    <label for='plan_<%= k %>'>
      <%= plan['ram'] %> MB RAM, <%= plan['storage'] %> GB Disk, <%= plan['bandwidth'] %> GB Bandwidth
      ($<%= plan['mrc'] %> USD)
    </label>
    <br/>
  <% end %>
</div>
<br/>

<div>
  I intend to install something like:

  <select id='os' name='os'>
    <option value=''>Undecided</option>
    <option value='linux'>Linux</option>
    <option value='freebsd'>FreeBSD</option>
    <option value='openbsd-6.0-amd64'>OpenBSD</option>
    <option value='ubuntu-14.04-amd64'>Ubuntu 14.04 or older</option>
  </select>
</div>

<table class='small-note'>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <div>
        We will optimize the VM parameters to suit the intended OS, but you can still install anything
        you like.
      </div>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

<%= render :partial => 'location', :locals => { :title => nil } %>

<table class='small-note'>
  <tr>
    <td class='caption'><strong>Note</strong>:</td>
    <td>
      <div>
        If you do not have an IP block for either of these locations, please contact <a href='mailto:support@arpnetworks.com'>support@arpnetworks.com</a> so we can add one.
      </div>
      <div>
        We apologize for the extra step, this will soon be automated.
      </div>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
